---
import Article from "../../../layouts/Article.astro";
import KeyTakeaway from "../../../components/KeyTakeaway.astro";
import InfoBox from "../../../components/InfoBox.astro";
import StepList from "../../../components/StepList.astro";
import Step from "../../../components/Step.astro";
import QuickFact from "../../../components/QuickFact.astro";
---

<Article
  title="How to Set Up Catan in Under 5 Minutes"
  description="A step-by-step guide to fast setup, including a resource organization trick that cuts time in half."
  game="catan"
  gameTitle="Catan"
  category="Guide"
  product="catan-resource-tokens"
  publishDate="2025-05-01"
>
  <p>
    Catan setup is the tax you pay before the fun starts. Sorting resource cards,
    shuffling number tokens, arranging hex tiles — it eats 10–15 minutes if you're
    not careful.
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaway answer="The secret to fast setup isn't speed — it's how you stored the game last time. Good teardown = instant setup." />

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 my-6">
    <QuickFact label="Typical setup" value="10–15 min" icon="🐌" />
    <QuickFact label="With this guide" value="Under 5 min" icon="⚡" />
    <QuickFact label="With proper storage" value="Under 3 min" icon="🚀" />
  </div>

  <h2>The Biggest Time Sink</h2>

  <p>
    The single thing that slows setup down the most is separating five types of
    resource cards from whatever jumbled state they were left in.
  </p>

  <InfoBox type="tip" title="The Golden Rule">
    Never mix resource types when packing up. Sort them back immediately after each game — it takes 30 seconds post-game but saves 5+ minutes pre-game. If you use 3D-printed resource tokens instead of cards, the sorting problem disappears entirely.
  </InfoBox>

  <h2>The 5-Step Speedrun</h2>

  <StepList>
    <Step number={1} title="Frame First" time="30 sec">
      Lay out the six ocean frame pieces. They only fit one way. If you store them pre-assembled (which they're designed for), this is instant.
    </Step>

    <Step number={2} title="Tiles — Randomize as You Place" time="60 sec">
      Shuffle the 19 terrain hexes face-down and place them into the frame one by one, flipping as you go. Random placement is the default and fastest approach.
    </Step>

    <Step number={3} title="Number Tokens — The Alphabet Trick" time="60 sec">
      The number tokens have small letters (a through r) on their backs. Place them in alphabetical order starting from a corner, spiraling inward. Skip the desert. This guarantees proper number distribution.
    </Step>

    <Step number={4} title="Cards & Bank" time="45 sec">
      If your resources are pre-sorted, just set out the five piles. Shuffle the development card deck. Place longest road and largest army cards to the side.
    </Step>

    <Step number={5} title="Player Setup" time="60 sec">
      Each player takes their color tray (5 settlements, 4 cities, 15 roads) and two building cost reference cards. Initial settlement placement happens during play.
    </Step>
  </StepList>

  <InfoBox type="info" title="The Alphabet Trick Explained">
    Store your number tokens pre-sorted in alphabetical order in a small bag. When you pull them out, you just go in order — no hunting for the right token. This single habit saves the most time.
  </InfoBox>

  <h2>Advanced: The Preset Map</h2>

  <p>
    For the absolute fastest setup, use a recommended beginner layout from the
    rulebook. These have fixed hex positions and fixed number placements. You can
    even photograph your favorite layout and recreate it from the photo in under
    2 minutes.
  </p>

  <h2>Storage Habits That Pay Off Every Game</h2>

  <div class="my-6 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
    <div class="p-4 bg-emerald-50 rounded-xl border border-emerald-100">
      <div class="text-lg mb-1">🧩</div>
      <p class="text-sm text-emerald-800">Ocean frame pieces stored assembled or rubber-banded together</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 bg-emerald-50 rounded-xl border border-emerald-100">
      <div class="text-lg mb-1">🔤</div>
      <p class="text-sm text-emerald-800">Number tokens in alphabetical order in a small bag</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 bg-emerald-50 rounded-xl border border-emerald-100">
      <div class="text-lg mb-1">📦</div>
      <p class="text-sm text-emerald-800">Resources separated by type using dividers or a token system</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 bg-emerald-50 rounded-xl border border-emerald-100">
      <div class="text-lg mb-1">🎨</div>
      <p class="text-sm text-emerald-800">Each player's pieces in their own bag with a reference card</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <InfoBox type="tip" title="The Real Insight">
    Most "setup time" in Catan is actually "recovery from bad teardown" time. Invest 2 minutes at the end of each game, and you'll never dread setup again.
  </InfoBox>
</Article>
